Now let me understand more deeply. The issue is specifically with `upsertWhitespaceBeforeMe` when called on the LBRACE node (first child of BLOCK). The problem is that when `treePrev` is null and `prevLeaf()` returns a node in a different parent, we can't just do `rawInsertBeforeMe` because that inserts the whitespace in the wrong parent.

Let me look at the `else` branch of `upsertWhitespaceBeforeMe`:

```kotlin
} else {
    val prevLeaf =
        requireNotNull(prevLeaf()) {
            "Can not upsert a whitespace if the first node is a non-leaf node"
        }
    prevLeaf.upsertWhitespaceAfterMe(text)
}
```

This `else` is for non-leaf nodes. If BLOCK (composite) calls `upsertWhitespaceBeforeMe`, it would call `prevLeaf.upsertWhitespaceAfterMe(text)` on the `)` character.

Then in `upsertWhitespaceAfterMe`:
```kotlin
val next = treeNext ?: nextLeaf()
```

For `)` (RPAR, last child of VALUE_PARAMETER_LIST), `treeNext` is null, so it uses `nextLeaf()`. But wait, `nextLeaf()` just walks the tree - it doesn't add children to the correct parent.

Actually, let me re-read the code. When `SpacingAroundCurlyRule` calls `node.upsertWhitespaceBeforeMe(" ")` where `node` is the LBRACE:

```kotlin
public fun ASTNode.upsertWhitespaceBeforeMe(text: String) {
    if (this is LeafElement) {
        if (this.elementType == WHITE_SPACE) {
            return replaceWhitespaceWith(text)
        }
        val previous = treePrev ?: prevLeaf()
        if (previous != null && previous.elementType == WHITE_SPACE) {
            previous.replaceWhitespaceWith(text)
        } else {
            PsiWhiteSpaceImpl(text).also { psiWhiteSpace ->
                (psi as LeafElement).rawInsertBeforeMe(psiWhiteSpace)
